      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the accepted QoI for comparative hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance on blood-contacting devices. RH directly supports the regulatory decision of whether the test device produces hemolysis comparable to or less than the predicate, which is the stated COU decision criterion."
